30 000 people against racism üí™
Last night I joined 30 000 people in the streets of Cologne to protest against racism in Germany.
Why? In Germany, politicians of the far-right party (AfD) have openly admitted their plans of mass deportations and depriving Germans with migrational history of their citizenship. While the AfD‚Äòs racist and anti-humanistic views are disgusting to most Germans, the party has been gaining huge support in national and regional opinion polls and many AfD supporters are calling for an ethnic and political cleansing. Does this sound familiar to something that happend in Germany not even 100 years ago? Unfortunately yes. Time to stand up.

Nightfall in the dunes.
I spent the sunset in the Wahiba Sands without my camera or drone, simply enjoying the vibe and great company in this otherworldly place. Long after the sun had set I decided to send up my drone just to see what it would look like. Unreal! The soft light of the fading day gave this place a whole new appearance. 
Thanks @sarahamalija for modeling and thanks @followthetracks.oman for leading us to this place! Check them out for your own personal Oman adventure.

Portraits from afar. ‚ú®
An rather unusual set of photos on this account, but somehow Oman inspired me to shoot more local culture and people. I don‚Äôt like being a camera-in-peoples-faces-tourist, so here‚Äôs a set of portraits from a far. A couple notes about each of these shots:

1. üìçFort Nizwa - I liked how the soft light matched the rounded shapes of this historical landmark.

2. üìçWahiba Sands - I was snapping portraits of a camel when suddenly a truck with smiling Omani passed by. Big fan of the camel‚Äôs lip.

3. üìçNizwa - Blue hour, neon lights and a lonely chair. I really enjoyed this scene, especially as two men walked by.

4. üìçSur harbour - I was snapping photos on a mountain by the bay when this heroic fisherman cruised through the scene.

5. üìçBidiyah - It was midday, but the smoke from burnt palm leaves created a soft atmosphere among the palm trees. 

6. üìçSomewhere in between - I loved the old Toyota trucks I saw all over Oman. Fun fact: the boy drove off by himself moments later.

7. üìçNizwa - Two strangers walking down jewellery lane. I really liked the look of the large arabic signs on every business. 

8. üìçSur beach - Loved watching all the different activities on the beach. Men landing boats, Women picknicking by the car, kids playing in the water, dogs, birds, everything.

9. üìçSultan Qaboos Grand Mosque - A family chilling on the steps of one of the worlds largest mosques. If felt truly peaceful.

This might be the longest caption ever, but I thought some people might enjoy the extra insights. Did you? ü§ö

All of these scenes happened along the designated Arabian Wold route by @followthetracks.oman. If you‚Äôre thinking about visiting Oman one day (which you should), check them out! üëâ @followthetracks.oman
